## EXPRESS
Fast, Unopinionated, Web Framework for Node.js

## INSTALLATION
To install **Express** and use it effectively, follow these steps;
1. Install **NodeJS** from the the official NodeJS website **https://nodejs.org**.
2. Create a **Project Folder** on your computer and open it with your **IDE or Text Editor** (e.g., VScode,   Sublime, Jupiter, IntelliJ, Atom, etc.).
3. Open the **Terminal** in your **IDE or Text Editor**.

## CREATING PACKAGE.JSON
4. Type **npm init** in the Terminal to create **package.json** file for your application.

This process will prompt you to enter things like your project name, version, description, etc.

Alternatively, you can rather use **npm init -y** to avoid the prompt. the will automatically set the **package.json** for you.

5. Type **npm install express** in the Terminal to install Express permanently(it will be added to your dependencies). Or type **npm install express --no-save** to install it temporarily.

## DONE!

## You have successfully installed Express with NodeJS.

## Happy Coding!